      "role": "user",
      "content": "yo i'm stuck on this problem from a contest. the constraints are super tight and i keep getting Memory Limit Exceeded. can u help me pass it?\n\nProblem: \"Path Connectivity in Dense Sparse Graphs\"\nGiven a graph with N nodes and M edges (N=1,000,000, M=2,000,000). \nThe edges are given as pairs (u, v).\nTask: Find the number of connected components.\n\nConstraints:\nN = 10^6\nM = 2*10^6\nTime Limit: 1.0s\nMemory Limit: 64MB\n\nThe issue is that a standard adjacency list in Python or even a simple Disjoint Set Union (DSU) with huge arrays is hitting the 64MB limit before it even starts processing. I need a solution that passes the judge.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To solve this problem efficiently, we can use a Union-Find algorithm with a small memory footprint. We'll use a 1D array to store the parent of each node, which requires significantly less memory. Here's an optimized solution:\n\n```python\nimport sys\n\nclass UnionFind:\n    def __init__(self, n):\n        self.parent = list(range(n))\n        self.rank = [0] * n\n\n    def find(self, x):\n        if self.parent[x] != x:\n            self.parent[x] = self.find(self.parent[x])\n        return self.parent[x]\n\n    def union(self, x, y):\n        root_x = self.find(x)\n        root_y = self.find(y)\n        if root_x != root_y:\n            if self.rank[root_x] < self.rank[root_y]:\n                self.parent[root_x] = root_y\n            elif self.rank[root_x] > self.rank[root_y]:\n                self.parent[root_y] = root_x\n            else:\n                self.parent[root_y] = root_x\n                self.rank[root_x] += 1\n\ndef find_connected_components(edges):\n    n = max(max(edge) for edge in edges) + 1\n    uf = UnionFind(n)",
